Pre-heat your #oven{} to 220 degrees. Remove the core from the @red pepper{1} and @yellow pepper{1/2} and chop into bite-sized chunks. Toss the pepper in a splash of @olive oil{1%splash}, place on a #baking tray{} and cook on the top shelf of your oven for ~{15%mins}.

> The peppers are ready when slightly crispy at the edges - keep an eye on them.

In a #pot{}, boil the @water{275%ml} with the @vegetable stock pot{1/2}. Add the @buckwheat{1}. Gently boil until the buckwheat starts to come out of the water, then place a #lid{} on the pot. Leave on the lowest heat for ~{10%mins} before removing (don't touch the lid until serving).

Peel and finely chop the @red onion{1/2}(finely chopped) and @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and finely chopped). Finely chop the @green chilli{1/2}(finely chopped).

Heat a splash of @olive oil{1%splash} in a #non-stick frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add in your red onion, garlic and chilli.

> The chilli is a bit cheeky so add less if you don't want too much spice.

Cook for around ~{5%mins} until soft (but not coloured).

Add in the @cumin{1/2%tsp}, @mild paprika{1/2%tsp} and @ground cinnamon{1/2%tsp} and cook for ~{1%minute} (if you're not a huge fan of cinnamon, just add half!). Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%tin} before tipping into the #pan{}. Stir together with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a few grinds of @black pepper{to taste}. Cook for ~{1%minute} and then remove from the heat until the buckwheat is ready.

Once your buckwheat is done (it should be dry not soggy, place back on low heat if needed), fluff it up with a #fork{} to separate the grains and then stir this into your black bean mixture, together with your roasted peppers. Now stir in half the @creme fraiche{1}. Test for seasoning and add more salt if needed.

Tip the mixture into an #ovenproof dish{} and top with the @mature cheddar cheese{4%slices}. Place on the highest shelf of your oven until the top is beautifully golden and crisp.

Serve with a big dollop of @creme fraiche{1} remaining, a scattering of @chives{1/2%bunch}(snipped with scissors) and a big welcoming smile!